ctual and political life of the time; it also allows the reader to learn about Constant's relations to his family and friends.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aConstant. 4aFrankreich. 4aGeschichte. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAnelli, Boris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAnelli, Boris.1 aCourtney, C.P.1 aCourtney, C.P., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRickard, Peter.1 aWood, Dennis, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWood, Dennis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348450453040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311093433540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110934335423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110934335/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014